[{"category":"section","location":"#pals_julia.jl","page":"Home","text":"Documentation for pals_julia.jl.","title":"pals_julia.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Installation","page":"Home","text":"# Install from local directory\nusing Pkg\nPkg.add(path=\"/path/to/pals_julia.jl\")","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Quick-Example","page":"Home","text":"import Pkg\nPkg.activate(joinpath(@__DIR__, \"..\"))\nimport pals_julia as pj\n\n# Parse YAML\nconfig = parse_yaml(\"\"\"\nserver:\n  host: localhost\n  port: 8080\nfeatures:\n  - auth\n  - logging\n\"\"\")\n\n# Access values\nhost = String(config[\"server\"][\"host\"])  # \"localhost\"\nport = Int(config[\"server\"][\"port\"])     # 8080\n\n# Create YAML\nnew_config = create_map()\nnew_config[\"name\"] = \"MyApp\"\nwrite_yaml(new_config, \"config.pals.yaml\")","title":"Quick Example"},{"category":"module","location":"#pals_julia.pals_julia","page":"Home","text":"pals-julia\n\nA Julia wrapper around yaml-cpp's YAML::Node.\n\nRepresents a YAML document node that can be a scalar, map, or sequence.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"pals_julia.pals_julia"},{"category":"method","location":"#pals_julia.emit_yaml-Tuple{pals_julia.YAMLNode}","page":"Home","text":"emit_yaml(node::YAMLNode; indent=2) -> String\n\nConvert a YAML node to a formatted string using an emitter.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"pals_julia.emit_yaml"},{"category":"function","location":"#pals_julia.get_lattices","page":"Home","text":"get_lattices(filename::String, lattice_name::String=\"\") -> Lattices\n\nParses a lattice file and returns the original, included, and expanded lattice nodes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"pals_julia.get_lattices"},{"category":"method","location":"#pals_julia.write_yaml-Tuple{pals_julia.YAMLNode, String}","page":"Home","text":"write_yaml(node::YAMLNode, filename::String) -> Bool\n\nWrite a YAML node to a file using an emitter with default formatting.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"pals_julia.write_yaml"},{"category":"method","location":"#pals_julia.write_yaml_advanced-Tuple{pals_julia.YAMLNode, String}","page":"Home","text":"write_yaml_advanced(node::YAMLNode, filename::String; options...) -> Bool\n\nWrite a YAML node to a file with full formatting control.\n\nArguments\n\nindent: Number of spaces for indentation (default: 2)\nflow_maps: Use flow style for maps (default: false)\nflow_seqs: Use flow style for sequences (default: false)\nbool_format: Boolean format - :yesno, :truefalse, or :onoff (default: :truefalse)\nnull_format: Null format - :tilde (~), :lower (null), :upper (NULL), or :camel (Null) (default: :lower)\nstring_format: String format - :auto, :single, :double, or :literal (default: :auto)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"pals_julia.write_yaml_advanced"},{"category":"method","location":"#pals_julia.write_yaml_formatted-Tuple{pals_julia.YAMLNode, String}","page":"Home","text":"write_yaml(node::YAMLNode, filename::String; \n           indent=2, flow_maps=false, flow_seqs=false) -> Bool\n\nWrite a YAML node to a file with emitter control.\n\nArguments\n\nindent: Number of spaces for indentation (default: 2)\nflow_maps: Use flow style {key: value} for maps (default: false)\nflow_seqs: Use flow style [item1, item2] for sequences (default: false)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"pals_julia.write_yaml_formatted"}]
